# Comprehensive Markdown Guide
## Introduction to Advanced Markdown Features

### 1. Text Formatting Basics

This is *italic* and this is **bold**
Here's ***bold italic*** text
~~Strikethrough~~ text
`inline code`

### 2. Lists

#### Ordered List
1. First item
2. Second item
   1. Sub-item 2.1
   2. Sub-item 2.2
3. Third item

#### Unordered List
* Item one
  * Sub-item
  * Sub-item
* Item two
* Item three

### 3. Blockquotes

> This is a simple blockquote
>> This is a nested blockquote
>>> Even deeper nesting

### 4. Code Blocks

```python
def hello_world():
    print("Hello, Markdown!")
    
class Example:
    def __init__(self):
        self.value = 42
```

```javascript
function calculateSum(a, b) {
    return a + b;
}
```

### 5. Tables

| Feature | Basic | Pro | Enterprise |
|---------|:------|:---:|----------:|
| Users | 10 | 100 | Unlimited |
| Storage | 5GB | 50GB | 500GB |
| Support | Email | 24/7 | Dedicated |
| Custom Domain | âŒ | âœ… | âœ… |
| Analytics | Basic | Advanced | Full Suite |

### 6. Images and Links

![Markdown Logo](https://markdown-here.com/img/icon256.png)
[Visit GitHub](https://github.com)

### 7. LaTeX Mathematical Expressions

Inline equation: $E = mc^2$

Block equation:
$$
\frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}
$$

$$
\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{1}{n^2} = \frac{\pi^2}{6}
$$

### 8. Task Lists

- [x] Write the introduction
- [x] Add code examples
- [ ] Complete documentation
- [ ] Review and publish

### 9. Horizontal Rules

---
***
___

### 10. Advanced Table with Alignment

| Left-aligned | Center-aligned | Right-aligned |
|:------------|:-------------:|-------------:|
| col 3 is | some wordy text | $1600 |
| col 2 is | centered | $12 |
| zebra stripes | are neat | $1 |

### 11. Definition Lists

Term 1
: Definition 1

Term 2
: Definition 2a
: Definition 2b

### 12. Footnotes

Here's a sentence with a footnote[^1].

[^1]: This is the footnote content.

### 13. Custom HTML

<details>
<summary>Click to expand!</summary>

This is hidden content that can be expanded.
</details>

<div align="center">
  <h3>Centered content</h3>
  <p>This entire section is centered</p>
</div>

### 14. Emoji Support

:smile: :heart: :thumbsup: :rocket:

### 15. Mermaid Diagrams

```mermaid
graph TD;
    A-->B;
    A-->C;
    B-->D;
    C-->D;
```
